		<div id="comment_body_64229662"><p>They historically had very cheap hydro, so lots of people were already heating electrically at COP=1. Their grid is dimensioned for that and they can return to it when necessary. Though the European electricity market bidding up their hydro makes it more expensive.</p><p>Governments in colder climates should be very careful with air source heatpumps, it's a grid disaster waiting to happen.</p></div>
	</div>

