	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64229094"><p>My Mitsubishi hit the limit in the last cold snap. At -5 F it was still putting out warmish air, but it was not keeping up with the losses from the wind. I had to start up the baseboards I have as backup.</p><p>In warmer weather like the typical 10 F above zero that is a normal winter nighttime temperature here it does fine.</p><p>It surprises me that Maine is pushing them, not only is it cold there, but it's damp and the outdoor unit will be frosting up quite often.</p></div>
	</div>

