	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64230118">40% isn't a bad rule of thumb for power plant efficiency - some do up to 60% but that's about it.  In the end it's got be less than Carnot efficiency which is 1 - T_cold/T_hot.  Since T_cold is going to be in the vicinity of 250-280K (on Earth anyway) you need a crazy hot heat source to do a lot better.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64230118">

