	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64229964"><p>I have had a number of coworkers in different real estate regulation jurisdictions fall into a trap with ground coupled heat pumps:  in many jurisdictions a ground-coupled heat pump is classified as a well, and those jurisdictions had regulations saying that in residential areas wells can only be installed on unimproved land. Once the foundation is poured it is no longer unimproved.  Check with your builder and building code office to determine if you need to drill the hole first before other construction s<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

